{"TopicId":179065,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Streetlights, but from Space","CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-18T07:18:28Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-18T07:18:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.theguardian.com/science/2018/oct/17/chinese-city-plans-to-launch-artificial-moon-to-replace-streetlights\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.theguardian.com/science/2018/oct/17/chinese-city-plans-to-launch-artificial-moon-to-replace-streetlights\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, someone thinks it would be great if they could put a satellite up there that would shine down on Earth during the night to produce \u0022dusk-like glow\u0022 which is, according to the article about 8 times as bright as moonlight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith moonlight being about one millionth as bright as Sun, it would take about\u00A0800 kW to power this monstrosity. That\u0027s 10 times the size of ISS solar array.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow, how to we cool this thing down?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-18T08:30:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot politics, but some Chinese city would probably await a tax inspection.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cassel","CreatedById":181728,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-18T08:39:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBest way to block ability of common person to observe stars?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-18T10:49:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223470286\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179065\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539851972\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181728\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cassel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Cassel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBest way to block ability of common person to observe stars?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot to mention the impact on fauna and flora.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-18T11:00:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFalse flag, people ! It\u0027s the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://youtu.be/xMxVBY70dPU\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Egiant land-burner\u003C/a\u003E !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-18T11:17:22Z\u0022 title=\u002210/18/2018 11:17  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 18, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by YNM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-18T11:00:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAn giant mirror should be able to do this too and cheaper, bonus is that you can put it in an higher orbit, geo might be an option.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nSoviet thought about it for some areas in Sibir.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-18T11:04:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn any case, I\u0027d argue such concentrated-light contraptions should count under space weapons.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cassel","CreatedById":181728,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-18T12:39:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223470339\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179065\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539860439\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAn giant mirror should be able to do this too and cheaper, bonus is that you can put it in an higher orbit, geo might be an option.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nSoviet thought about it for some areas in Sibir.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, but it turned out to be cheaper to spray from balloons substances focusing the solar energy ;-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-18T12:39:57Z\u0022 title=\u002210/18/2018 12:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 18, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Cassel\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-18T12:45:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223470339\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179065\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539860439\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAn giant mirror should be able to do this too and cheaper, bonus is that you can put it in an higher orbit, geo might be an option.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nSoviet thought about it for some areas in Sibir.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure, it would still need to be very large. Not inconceivably large, but about twice the size of ISS array, plus control mechanism.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223470341\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179065\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539860681\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298447\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022YNM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, YNM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn any case, I\u0027d argue such concentrated-light contraptions should count under space weapons.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot at this power level. If it can concentrate all its power to an area of 100 m^2 (10 m\u00A0x 10 m square) it would deliver 8 kW/m^2 which would give you a decent tan, but is far from death-ray. For example, industrial fiber lasers (that are in several kW power range) focus all that energy to a tiny spot of about 0.1 mm^2. That means the energy density is on the order of 10 million times higher.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-18T13:39:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf launch a disco ball they can illuminate all their cities.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-18T13:40:06Z\u0022 title=\u002210/18/2018 01:40  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 18, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ultimate Steve","CreatedById":161505,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-18T16:13:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEveryone freaks out about Rocket Lab\u0027s tiny insignificant blinking disco ball, imagine the backlash if this were launched...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-19T00:06:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223470378\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179065\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539866713\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245577\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Shpaget\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 hours ago, Shpaget said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Eat this power level.\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can\u0027t be too sure of their true capabilities...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/xMxVBY70dPU?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022459\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d prefer to \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Die_Another_Day\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Edie another day\u003C/a\u003E than a space streetlight today.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-19T08:44:27Z\u0022 title=\u002210/19/2018 08:44  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 19, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by YNM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"insert_name","CreatedById":150339,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-19T02:19:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow would they keep it over the city if its not equatorial?\u00A0 Also this seems like it would throw off a lot of star\u00A0 and moon trackers on spacecraft,\u00A0 causing all sorts of diplomatic issues. Not to mention that the size of this thing would make JWST look like a childs toy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mad Rocket Scientist","CreatedById":139256,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-19T03:18:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it\u00A0really\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Ethat\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0expensive to install streetlights? The largest issue I think would be the impact on animals which rely on the moon (or darkness) for stuff. Also people with skylights who want to sleep. It does say this in the article: \u0022the precise illumination range could be controlled within tens of metres\u0022 although it\u0027s unclear how that would be:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\na) Possible\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nb) Cheaper than streetlights, even over 100s of years of electrical costs\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nc) Not a weapon\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis reminds me of the time I considered using airships with IR spotlights and night-vision contact lenses for every citizen to replace streetlights.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Reactordrone","CreatedById":110060,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-19T04:11:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA new Znamya. Should be an interesting test if nothing else.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.reddit.com/r/space/comments/6gnilu/progress_spacecraft_testing_the_cosmos1/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.reddit.com/r/space/comments/6gnilu/progress_spacecraft_testing_the_cosmos1/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-19T08:45:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223470915\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179065\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539919108\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139256\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mad Rocket Scientist\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Mad Rocket Scientist said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022the\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E precise illumination range could be controlled within tens of metres\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u0022\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll be damned if Eon Productions managed to get an idea years before they went for it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sh1pman","CreatedById":147869,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-19T15:17:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\nThe plan from Chinese leaders is to put three small, highly reflective satellites in orbit by around 2020. These satellites would reflect light at night and be be around 8 times brighter than the light from a full moon, enough to brighten the streets of Chengdu without spending any electricity on lighting. Such a plan, if it works, could save the city nearly $250 million in electricity costs per year, more than enough to justify the cost of the satellites.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\nEven though Chengdu wants three reflective satellites, they wouldn\u2019t all operate at the same time. They\u2019d work on a rotation, and only one would light up the city at a time. Each satellite would provide light in a circle between 6 and 25 miles wide, enough to guarantee coverage of at least the inner city, and sometimes enough to cover the entire metropolitan area.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\nOfficials also stated that these satellites could also be used to light up areas that don\u2019t receive much artificial lighting, like rural areas or the sites of disasters like earthquakes or hurricanes. That\u2019s assuming that they work as intended, of course. But if they do, it could help plenty of other cities end the\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.popularmechanics.com/science/environment/a15337939/light-pollution-science/\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#21836f;\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Escourge of light pollution\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.popularmechanics.com/space/satellites/a23903386/china-moons-reflective-satellites-street-lights/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.popularmechanics.com/space/satellites/a23903386/china-moons-reflective-satellites-street-lights/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuke","CreatedById":10883,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-19T16:11:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhow many astronauts does it take to screw in a light bulb?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rakaydos","CreatedById":101988,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-19T18:00:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOut of curiosity, what would be the spread of overlapping red/green lasers from LEO or GEO to the surface? Would it be plausable to illuminate a single street with an orbital laser array? (assuming it was never cloudy)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-19T20:16:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223471223\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179065\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539962251\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022147869\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sh1pman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, sh1pman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut if they do, it could help plenty of other\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E cities end the\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.popularmechanics.com/science/environment/a15337939/light-pollution-science/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#21836f;\u0022\u003Escourge of light pollution\u003C/a\u003E.\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeems more like light pollution on a planetary scale.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sh1pman","CreatedById":147869,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-19T20:27:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223471434\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179065\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539980207\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150244\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nightside\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, Nightside said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeems more like light pollution on a planetary scale.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool stuff nonetheless.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-19T20:41:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.nextbigfuture.com/2018/10/chengdu-launching-satellite-to-create-8x-full-moon-lighting.html/amp\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.nextbigfuture.com/2018/10/chengdu-launching-satellite-to-create-8x-full-moon-lighting.html/amp\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s getting crazier.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow they are talking about eventually having this thing illuminating ground based solar farms 24/7, presumably at daylight illumination level.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ultimate Steve","CreatedById":161505,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-19T21:05:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223471453\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179065\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539981668\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245577\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Shpaget\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 minutes ago, Shpaget said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow they are talking about eventually having this thing illuminating ground based solar farms 24/7, presumably at daylight illumination level.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm... If we put the farms where nobody lives, this I could actually get behind. But don\u0027t plants use the day/night cycle as a regulator for breathing, or am I remembering?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-19T21:13:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223471464\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179065\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539983100\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161505\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ultimate Steve\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Ultimate Steve said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm... If we put the farms where nobody lives, this I could actually get behind. But don\u0027t plants use the day/night cycle as a regulator for breathing, or am I remembering?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe you are correct, but at the very least, a variety of animals rely on the day night cycle.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-19T22:07:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223471453\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179065\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539981668\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245577\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Shpaget\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Shpaget said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E they are talking about eventually having this thing illuminating ground based solar farms 24/7, presumably\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E at daylight illumination level\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E.\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooking even more this way then.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/xMxVBY70dPU?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022459\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}